"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-what-time-team-sa-chad-le-clos-in-action-friday-02-august-2024\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbWhat time is Team SA, Chad le Clos in action on Friday?  Here are all the times when Team SA athletes will be in action at the Olympics on Friday, including Chad le Clos.  Team SA start Friday with four medals, withTatjana Smith (gold and silver) adding to the bronze medalssecured by the men's sevens rugby and Alan Hatherly, lifting them to 18th place on the overall table.  Team SA areinvolved in five sports on the day, with Chad le Clos in action on Friday.  SA TIMES FOR OLYMPIC ACTION ON FRIDAY:  ATHLETICS  Men's 1500m, round 1, heats (11.10am):Ryan Mphahlele  Men's 1500m, round 1, heats (11.21am):Tshepo Tshite  Women's 800m, round 1, heats (7.54pm):Prudence Sekgodiso  Men's shot put, qualification, Group B (8.10pm):Kyle Blignaut  Men's 10 000m, final (9.20pm):Adriaan Wildschutt  ROWING  Men's Pair B, final (10.42am):John Smith and Christopher Baxter  GOLF  Men's Individual, second round  9.22am:Erik van Rooyen (67)  11.33am:Christiaan Bezuidenhout (71)  HOCKEY  Men's Pool A (7.45pm):Team SA vs France  SWIMMING  Men's 100m butterfly, heats (11.03am):Matthew Sates, Clad le Clos  Women's 200m IM, heats (11.30am):Rebecca Meder  \\\"I am the third oldest male swimmer at these Games, so in those terms I am something of a pensioner,\\\" Le Clos toldTeam South Africa.  \\\"And in spite of picking up a shoulder tear in training, I have come to Paris believing I have a chance. I have raced with injuries before.  \\\"I think that the semi-final will be the harder race, because there will be 16 swimmers going for a place in the final. I am hoping to get there and once I do I will be chasing another dream. I am a warrior, a born racer.  \\\"Yes, I have had an injury the last two weeks. I went to the medical team as soon as I arrived from Montpellier and had it checked out. The first thing I did after that was head for the dining hall!  \\\"I am here to enjoy the experience, even if I do not think it's my last, and give of my best.\\\"  South Africa's most decorated Olympian of all time with four medals, Chad Le Closscored one of the sensations of London 2012, defeating the great Michael Phelps in the 200m butterfly.  Four years later, he shared silver with the American great in a stunning 100m butterfly final in Rio.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Reg